  <static seed="1195" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalExpressionAlgebraSkills/divideRationalExpressions40.pg">
    <statement><p>Simplify this expression, and if applicable, write the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{25y^{2}-4}{5y^{2}-8y-4}} \div ({2-5y}) =}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{1}{y-2}, y\ne 0.4\hbox{ and }y\ne -0.4</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{25y^{2}-4}{5y^{2}-8y-4}} \div {2-5y} 
      \amp = {\frac{25y^{2}-4}{5y^{2}-8y-4}} \div \frac{{2-5y}}{1} \\
      \amp = {\frac{25y^{2}-4}{5y^{2}-8y-4}} \cdot {\frac{1}{2-5y}} \\
      \amp =  \frac{{\left(5y+2\right)\mathopen{}\left(5y-2\right)}}{{\left(5y+2\right)\mathopen{}\left(y-2\right)}} \cdot \frac{{1}}{{-\left(5y-2\right)}} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{1}{y-2}, y\ne 0.4\hbox{ and }y\ne -0.4}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factors <m>5y+2</m> and <m>5y-2</m> were canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification are <m>y \ne {{\frac{2}{5}}\; and \;-{\frac{2}{5}}}</m>.</p>
</solution>
